        <article><![CDATA[<div class="body conbody">
<p class="p">Define facets to help your users refine their search results using dynamically-generated categories.</p>
<ol id="configure-facets__ol_kjj_ssk_2nb" class="ol"><li class="li">Edit the search application configuration that you want to configure a facet for.</li><li class="li">In the Facets related list, click <strong><span class="ph uicontrol">New</span></strong>.</li><li class="li">On the Facet form, fill in the fields.
<dl class="dl"><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Name</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Unique name for the facet.</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Order</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Numeric display order for the facet. Facets with lower order values display first.</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Facet Field</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Name of the field the facet uses to categorize search results for refinement.</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Option Limit</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Maximum number of distinct field values to display for the facet.</dd><dt class="dt dlterm"><strong>Label</strong></dt><dd class="dd">Display label used in the application for the facet.</dd></dl>
</li><li class="li">Click <strong><span class="ph uicontrol">Submit</span></strong>.</li></ol>
</div>]]></article>
